      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just stress. stress is a reaction to something that already happened. this is different. it's like a precursor. i felt the pressure exactly 30 seconds before the sell-off hit the tape. it's too precise to be just anxiety. it feels more like a signal, like my body is tuned into the same frequency as the data flow. don't u think there could be some kind of bio-frequency thing going on where high-speed data bursts actually affect the local environment?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
